.TH "ib_alloc_mr" 9 "ib_alloc_mr" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ib_alloc_mr \- Allocates a memory region
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct ib_mr *" ib_alloc_mr
.BI "(struct ib_pd *pd "  ","
.BI "enum ib_mr_type mr_type "  ","
.BI "u32 max_num_sg "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pd" 12
protection domain associated with the region
.IP "mr_type" 12
memory region type
.IP "max_num_sg" 12
maximum sg entries available for registration.
.SH "NOTES"
Memory registeration page/sg lists must not exceed max_num_sg.
For mr_type IB_MR_TYPE_MEM_REG, the total length cannot exceed
max_num_sg * used_page_size.
